\begin_body

\begin_layout Standard
\align center
0xDACC
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\align center
2024 Design Document
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\align center
Secure MISC
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
\begin_inset Newpage newpage
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
\align center

\series bold
Proposed Attest Changes
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
Store attestation PIN as a hash with enough rounds that it takes approximately
 2 seconds.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
- Limits brute force attempts
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
- Makes PIN unable to be extracted from flash
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
Store attestation data encrypted with symmetric key as 1 round less of attestati
on pin hash 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
- Also limits brute force and makes PIN unreadable from flash
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
Altogether these changes will help meet SR3 and SR4
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
\begin_inset Newpage newpage
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
\align center

\series bold
Proposed Replace Changes
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
Store replacement token as a hash
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
- Makes token unable to be extracted from flash
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
Verify component authenticity
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
1.
 Store an asymmetric public key in flash
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
2.
 Generate a random number using onboard TRNG
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
3.
 Ask new component to sign random number
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
4.
 Verify using onboard public key
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
Altogether these changes will help meet SR1 and SR2
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Newpage newpage
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\align center

\series bold
Proposed Boot Changes
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
Verify integrity of all 3 boards
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
- Store public keys A and D on AP
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
- Store public key B on Component1
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
- Store public key C on Component2
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
1.
 AP generates a random number and asks Component1 to sign
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
2.
 AP verifies signature
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
3.
 Component1 generates a random number and asks AP to sign
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
4.
 Component1 verifies signature
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
5.
 Component2 generates a random number and asks AP to sign
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
6.
 Component2 verifies signature
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
7.
 AP generates a random number and asks Component2 to sign
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
8.
 AP verifies signature
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\emph on
If any signatures are invalid, stop immediately and shut down.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
\align left
Altogether these changes will help meet SR1 and SR2.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\align center
\begin_inset Newpage newpage
\end_inset


\series bold
Proposed Secure TX & RX Changes
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
Public KEX
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
- Generate private key using RNG
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
- Create an encrypted channel even though unnessecary.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
- Confidentiality will be provided to make RE'ing just a tiny bit harder
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
- Encrypt packets with negotiated key
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
- Negotiate HMAC key over new channel
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
- Append HMAC to all packets before encrypting
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
\align left
Altogether these changes will help meet SR5.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Newpage newpage
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
\align center

\series bold
Other
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
Secure DAPLink firmware for RISC-V chip
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
- Only execute signed code
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
- Disable the DAPLINK flashing utility
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
- Disable code debugging
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
All of the above objectives are futile if the attacker can simply modify
 the flash or just set a breakpoint where the validation happens.
 By not allowing the chip to be debugged (easily) and only allowing signed
 code to be run, security becomes a lot more reasonable.
\end_layout

